                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-02T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 2, 1933—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Following from Consul General Mukden: February 1, 4 p.m. According to
                    confidential information believed trustworthy 19 troop trains will move from
                    Chinchow to Suichung and Shanhaikwan February 2nd or 3rd.</p>
                <p>All indications point to Jehol drive starting within a few days when military are
                    expected to issue an official statement.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
